    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eustis</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 5,
                                        1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At my conference with minister for foreign affairs he informed me
                                that he had received that morning the record in Waller’s case,
                                including the evidence. He said that it would take several days for
                                translation of documents and his examination; that he would then
                                communicate to me his decision in the matter. I urged upon him
                                prompt action. Waller family left early this morning, steamer <hi rend="italic">Amsterdam.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eustis</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
